<reg_short_dscr>:
Cellbus configuration
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Sets the minimum distance between grants to an internal port. Extra grants are disabled when configured value is 0, otherwise the port seeks extra bandwidth, and the minimum distance in clock cycles is given by this value. The replications are for internal CPU 0, internal CPU 1, VDs.

The minimum value accepted is 12. The internal ports will need a delay of 12 at the switch to a new frame, which will reduce the total bandwidth a bit for some frame sizes.

The bandwidth with a grant value of N with a core frequency of f MHz will grant 0.67f/N Gbps for smallest frames.
Ex: A value of 12 grants:
 23Gbps at 416 MHz, 
 28Gbps at 500 MHz,
 35Gbps at 625 MHz.
